The paper discusses the integration of robotics and neural network simulators, which suggests a focus on robotics and/or neural networks. The use of ROS and MUSIC also suggests a focus on software and middleware. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also specifically mentions spiking neural networks, which suggests a focus on computational neuroscience, placing it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, placing it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses closed-loop experiments, which suggests a focus on systems and control, placing it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses reinforcement learning, which suggests a focus on machine learning, placing it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
